text.tspan: As the snake's head grows closer to a powerup,
A solid gray block indicates an impassable obstacle.
If the snake makes contact with a gray block, it dies.
The absence of a gray border around the level indicates
that the snake may utilize "screen wrapping".
That is, if the snake travels past the edge of the screen,
it may appear again on the opposite edge and not die.
A wormhole may exist between two separate sets of points.
Each entrance/exit appears as a contigious strip of colored tiles.
When the snake makes contact with an entrance,
it will continue its travels from the corresponding exit.
Upon exiting, the snake's heading may have changed.
Multiple wormholes may exist on the map at once.
Each wormhole has a distinct color.
The wormholes arrangement can aid puzzle design.
